# evalv2 panics in `DerefValue` when processing a specific CUE input
# discovered via oss-fuzz, reproducing on both v0.9.2 and v0.10.1.
# https://cuelang.org/issue/3570
#todo:inline: hard — cycle semantics require @test(err, code=cycle) and careful scoping
-- in.cue --
foo: foo: 25 | 44
foo
foo: foo
-- out/compile --
--- in.cue
{
  foo: {
    foo: (25|44)
  }
  〈0;foo〉
  foo: 〈0;foo〉
}
-- out/evalalpha --
Errors:
2 errors in empty disjunction:
conflicting values {foo:{foo:(25|44)},foo,foo:foo} and 25 (mismatched types struct and int):
    ./in.cue:1:1
    ./in.cue:1:11
    ./in.cue:2:1
conflicting values {foo:{foo:(25|44)},foo,foo:foo} and 44 (mismatched types struct and int):
    ./in.cue:1:1
    ./in.cue:1:16
    ./in.cue:2:1

Result:
(_|_){
  // [eval] 2 errors in empty disjunction:
  // conflicting values {foo:{foo:(25|44)},foo,foo:foo} and 25 (mismatched types struct and int):
  //     ./in.cue:1:1
  //     ./in.cue:1:11
  //     ./in.cue:2:1
  // conflicting values {foo:{foo:(25|44)},foo,foo:foo} and 44 (mismatched types struct and int):
  //     ./in.cue:1:1
  //     ./in.cue:1:16
  //     ./in.cue:2:1
  foo: (struct){
    foo: (_){ _ }
  }
}
